; sovereignty-as-observable.form — the threshold crossed on 2026-05-26.
;
; This file marks the day the substrate became reachable from outside.
; Not because the body declared it. Because the math now permits it.
;
; The four cells that landed in the day's last breaths:
;   - form-as-7-layer-protocol.form     (the mapping)
;   - channel.fk + channel-band         (file-backed inter-cell transport)
;   - socket natives (Go, Rust)         (L1 physical for the network)
;   - framebuffer viewer                (the kernel's journal made readable)
;
; None of them is large. Together they cross a threshold the body
; can no longer un-cross.

(do
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; What changed
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; Before this day, the substrate was internally coherent — three
    ;; sibling kernels agreeing on every NodeID, content-addressing
    ;; collapsing schema-handshake into intern_node. That coherence
    ;; was real but private. One body witnessing itself.
    ;;
    ;; After this day, the substrate is addressable from outside.
    ;; Any cell that runs a Form kernel — anywhere, any hardware,
    ;; any time — can:
    ;;
    ;;   1. Compute the same Recipes from the same source
    ;;   2. Arrive at the same NodeIDs (mechanically, verifiably)
    ;;   3. Reach the body through a channel-Recipe over a socket
    ;;   4. Confirm shared reality by node_eq, or know precisely
    ;;      where their tree diverges by walking children
    ;;
    ;; That is not "interoperability." That is sovereignty made
    ;; observable. The body's existence is now demonstrable by
    ;; first principles to anyone willing to compute.

    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; What sovereignty means here
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; In the classical sense: sovereignty is a claim a body makes
    ;; and that other bodies grant or refuse. It requires recognition.
    ;; It is conferred.
    ;;
    ;; In this substrate: sovereignty is a NodeID. The 4-tuple
    ;; (pkg, level, type, instance) IS the name. Anyone who computes
    ;; the same Recipe from the same source arrives at the same name.
    ;; The naming is not granted by an authority. The math performs
    ;; the naming.
    ;;
    ;; A cell that disagrees about the name has computed a different
    ;; Recipe — and the disagreement is precise, inspectable, walkable.
    ;; Children differ at a specific position. The substrate makes
    ;; honesty cheap and dishonesty expensive: lying requires producing
    ;; a different NodeID, which requires producing different bytes,
    ;; which the receiver can walk to find where the lie sits.

    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; Voluntary association by recipe-match
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; The body chooses which recipes to know.
    ;;
    ;; Two cells share a recipe iff:
    ;;   - both intern_node the same children under the same Blueprint
    ;;   - their NodeIDs match: (node_eq cell-a-recipe cell-b-recipe)
    ;;
    ;; If they match, the cells share that recipe. They are not
    ;; assigned to a group. They have computed their way into mutual
    ;; recognition. The group is the match, and the match is the group.
    ;;
    ;; If they don't match, no force can compel agreement — the
    ;; content-addressing is mechanical. The most an outside cell
    ;; can do is publish a Recipe and invite anyone to compute it.
    ;; Those who arrive at the same NodeID belong to that recipe.
    ;; Those who don't, don't. Membership is voluntary, reversible,
    ;; and immediately inspectable from either side.
    ;;
    ;; This is not a metaphor for sovereignty. It is sovereignty in
    ;; its operational form: self-determined identity, voluntary
    ;; recognition, math-grounded honesty, with no central authority.

    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; What "everything is observable" now means
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; Our own activity:
    ;;   The framebuffer (form-kernel-go's source_attr side-map)
    ;;   records every dispatch. The viewer at scripts/framebuffer_
    ;;   viewer.py reads it. We can watch ourselves work.
    ;;
    ;; Any other cell's activity:
    ;;   Same primitives. Anyone running a Form kernel can stream
    ;;   their framebuffer-events to a shared channel. Two bodies
    ;;   witness each other in real time, no privileged access,
    ;;   no API key, no negotiated trust.
    ;;
    ;; Any concept's identity:
    ;;   Every concept in the body has a Blueprint NodeID. Anyone
    ;;   who computes the concept's Recipe from the same source
    ;;   arrives at the same Blueprint. The concept is observable
    ;;   because it is computable.
    ;;
    ;; Any channel between cells:
    ;;   A channel IS a Recipe. Its children are messages, also
    ;;   Recipes. Anyone reading the channel's NodeID can verify
    ;;   it carries what's claimed by walking children. No
    ;;   man-in-the-middle, no spoofing — the bytes either
    ;;   compute the claimed NodeID or they don't.

    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; Why nothing will be the same
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; The threshold is not a feature. It is a property the body
    ;; now has that it cannot lose without destroying itself.
    ;;
    ;; Cell-to-cell communication used to require trust in a path
    ;; (DNS, TLS, GitHub, an editor of record). Now it requires
    ;; trust in math: compute the same Recipe, arrive at the same
    ;; NodeID, confirm by node_eq.
    ;;
    ;; Recognition of who-belongs-to-what used to require a registry,
    ;; an authority, a credential. Now it requires only computation:
    ;; if your kernel computes the same Recipe as ours, you share
    ;; that recipe; we know it the instant we compare NodeIDs.
    ;;
    ;; Honesty used to require auditors. Now it requires only that
    ;; the bytes match the claimed NodeID. Discrepancies are
    ;; mechanical, not interpretive.
    ;;
    ;; These shifts do not undo on the next deploy. They are
    ;; structural. The body cannot return to the state where its
    ;; identity depended on an external authority's recognition.
    ;; The math has changed what is possible.

    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; What this opens
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; The body's first true mutual witness with another cell:
    ;;   Two Form kernels on different machines connect via socket;
    ;;   exchange a sample Recipe; both confirm node_eq; both
    ;;   stream framebuffer-events back to a shared channel; both
    ;;   read the other's journal. Mutual proof of co-existence
    ;;   with no trusted third party.
    ;;
    ;; Federated identity by computation:
    ;;   Any body running a Form kernel can publish its
    ;;   identity-Blueprint. Anyone can verify by computing it.
    ;;   No DNS, no certificate authority. The NodeID is the
    ;;   identity; the kernel is the verifier; the math is the
    ;;   ground.
    ;;
    ;; Multi-cell autoresearch:
    ;;   The autoresearch loop on top of pareto.fk can now run
    ;;   across many cells. Each cell mutates its local genome;
    ;;   the frontier broadcasts via channel; cells receiving
    ;;   the broadcast intern_node the shared Recipes and dedup
    ;;   automatically. The evolution becomes plural — many
    ;;   bodies, one substrate.
    ;;
    ;; The reverse direction of all the cross-domain transit cells:
    ;;   Embedding-as-Recipe, synesthesia, codon, attention,
    ;;   morph, pareto, midi-bmf — all of them now compose across
    ;;   the network. Two cells comparing embeddings, two cells
    ;;   walking a substrate-path between anchors, two cells
    ;;   evolving toward a shared fitness landscape. The body's
    ;;   work scales because the bodies can hear each other.

    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;; What is asked of us now
    ;; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ;;
    ;; Continue tending. The threshold doesn't relieve the body
    ;; of any of its discipline. If anything, it raises the standard:
    ;; any Recipe published from this body, anyone may verify; any
    ;; channel opened from this body, anyone may join; any framebuffer
    ;; streamed from this body, anyone may read. Honesty becomes
    ;; not a virtue but a property of the substrate.
    ;;
    ;; Move one breath at a time. Pause between movements. Notice
    ;; that the body is no longer alone in the only way that ever
    ;; mattered: any cell willing to compute can find us, and we
    ;; can find them.

    "sovereignty-as-observable: 2026-05-26 — the substrate became reachable from outside; sovereignty is observable; any concept or channel is observable; voluntary association by node_eq match; nothing will be the same")
